title: Hôtel Dassault - Artcurial
description:
The Hôtel Marcel Dassault was built in 1844, with some alterations having been made in 1952 after it was bought by Marcel Dassault.  Today the Hôtel Marcel Dassault is an art venue unique in Europe.  The interior of the neo-classical edifice was remodeled by Jean-Michel Wilmotte to mark its launch as a temple of the arts.

Since summer 2002 the Hôtel has housed a Bookshop, a Gallery of artworks in limited editions, and the offices of the auction firm Artcurial.

Tel : 01.42.99.20.20
      01.42.99.16.22

http://galerie.artcurial.com/fr/

title: Church of Saint Peter of Montmartre
description:
This is the parish church for the area of Montmartre and is much smaller than the nearby Basilica of the Sacred Heart. According to the earliest biography of Saint Ignatius Loyola, the church is the location at which the vows were taken that led to the founding of the Society of Jesus (the Jesuits).

Les grands guichets du Carrousel
description: Le guichet désignait une ouverture pour le passage des piétons dans une porte cochère, un petit battant en découpe dans un grand battant. Cela a donné leur nom aux « Guichets du Louvre » par exemple, bien qu'ils soient des portes simples sur des ouvertures maçonnées séparées entre les piétons et les voitures.

title: St Stephen Greek Orthodox Church

It was built in the 1890's and funded mainly by members of the Skylitsis Family. The architect was Vaudremere. i have seen it refered to as St Etienne. Is this a french version of Stephen ?
